{"questionId":"22320737","questionHtml":"<p>Find the first time after <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>12</mn><mo>:</mo><mn>00</mn></math> when the depth is equal to <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math>. Give your answer to the nearest minute.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>equating their expression to&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong><em>(M1)</em></strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mo> </mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>30</mn><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>OR&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mo> </mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>6</mn></mfrac><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn></math></strong></p>\n<p><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>64904</mn><mo>…</mo></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em>(A1)</em></strong></p>\n<p><strong><em><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>6</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>39</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mi>pm</mi></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>18</mn><mo>:</mo><mn>39</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; A1</em></strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note: </strong>Follow through within the part for the final <strong><em>A1</em></strong>; this mark is awarded for expressing <strong>their</strong> intermediate answer (seen) as a time correct to the nearest minute.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22320737","referenceCode":"24M.1.SL.TZ1.7c","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find the first time after 12:00 w